local rs_output = {}
rs_output.__index = rs_output

function rs_output:new(side)
	local object_table = {side = side}
	setmetatable(object_table, self)
	return object_table
end



function rs_output:enable()
print(self.side, "enable")
	rs.setOutput(self.side ,true)
end



function rs_output:disable()
print(self.side, "disable")
	rs.setOutput(self.side ,false)
end



function rs_output:get_input()
	return rs.getInput(self.side)
end




local gearshift = rs_output:new("right")
local sticker = rs_output:new("top")


sticker:enable()
sleep(0.2)
sticker:disable()
gearshift:enable()
sleep(10)
gearshift:disable()

title: Password Computer Craft with moden
content:
-----PREFERENCES/VARIABLES-----
local pin = 1528
local maxtries = 3
local locktime = 60 --seconds
local waittotry = 3 --seconds
local redstoneSide = "left"
local modemSide = "top"
local remoteMonitorName = "monitor_0" -- nome do monitor remoto na rede

local tries = 0
local input = ""
local keypad = {
  {1,2,4},
  {2,7,4},
  {3,12,4},
  {4,2,6},
  {5,7,6},
  {6,12,6},
  {7,2,8},
  {8,7,8},
  {9,12,8},
  {0,7,10}
}

-----FUNCTIONS-----
function checkClick(t,x,y)
  for i,v in pairs(t) do
    local num,cx,cy = unpack(v)
    if (x >= cx) and (x <= cx + 2) and (y == cy) then
      return true,num
    end
  end
  return false
end

function numClick(num)
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setCursorPos", (5 + (string.len(input) * 2)), 2)
  input = input .. num
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "write", "*")

  if (string.len(input) == 4) then
    if (tostring(pin) == input) then
      monAction("Access Granted")
      doorOpen()
      monReset(true)
      input = ""
      tries = 0
    else
      input = ""
      tries = tries + 1
      if (tries >= maxtries) then
        monReset()
        peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setBackgroundColor", colors.red)
        monAction("TERMINAL LOCKED")
        sleep(locktime)
        os.reboot()
      end
      monAction("Access Denied")
      sleep(waittotry)
      monReset(true)
    end
  end
end

function monAction(mess)
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setCursorPos", 1, 1)
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "clearLine")
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "write", mess)
end

function monReset(isClear)
  if (isClear) then peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "clearLine") end
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setCursorPos", 5, 2)
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "write", "_ _ _ _")
end

function doorOpen()
  redstone.setOutput(redstoneSide, true)
  sleep(3)
  redstone.setOutput(redstoneSide, false)
end

-----BEGIN MAIN-----
local modem = peripheral.wrap(modemSide)
if not modem then error("Modem n?o encontrado!") end

-- Ativar rede de perif?ricos
modem.open(0)
print("Conectando ao monitor remoto...")

-- Espera o monitor remoto aparecer
while not peripheral.isPresent(remoteMonitorName) do
  print("Aguardando monitor remoto...")
  sleep(2)
end

peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setTextScale", 0.5)
peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setBackgroundColor", colors.red)
peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setTextColor", colors.black)
peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "clear")

for i,v in pairs(keypad) do
  local num,x,y = unpack(v)
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setCursorPos", x, y)
  peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "write", " " .. num .. " ")
end

peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setBackgroundColor", colors.black)
peripheral.call(remoteMonitorName, "setTextColor", colors.white)
monReset()

print("Sistema iniciado com monitor remoto via modem.")

while true do
  local event, side, x, y = os.pullEvent("monitor_touch")
  validClick,num = checkClick(keypad,x,y)
  if (validClick) then
    numClick(num)
  end
end

title: RedstoneStarter
content:
-- controller.lua
-- Steuert das Startsignal f√ºr alle Musik-Computer
-- Version 1.0

local CONTROL_FILE = "disk/control.txt"
local TRIGGER_SIDE = "back"  -- <--- Seite hier anpassen (z.B. "left", "right", "back" usw.)

-- -----------------------------
-- Hilfsfunktion: schreibt die Control-Datei
-- -----------------------------
local function writeControl(play, startTime)
    local f = fs.open(CONTROL_FILE, "w")
    f.writeLine("play=" .. tostring(play))
    f.writeLine("startTime=" .. tostring(startTime))
    f.close()
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Hauptschleife
-- -----------------------------
print("Musikcontroller aktiv.")
print("Warte auf Redstone-Signal an Seite: " .. TRIGGER_SIDE)

-- Sicherstellen, dass Datei existiert
writeControl(false, 0)

while true do
    -- Auf steigende Flanke warten (Signal AN)
    if redstone.getInput(TRIGGER_SIDE) then
        local startTime = os.epoch("utc") + 1000 -- Start in 1 Sekunde
        print("Signal erkannt! Starte alle Ger√§te in 1 Sekunde...")
        writeControl(true, startTime)

        -- 2 Sekunden warten, damit alle Ger√§te starten
        sleep(2)

        -- Dann Signal zur√ºcksetzen
        writeControl(false, startTime)
        print("Startsignal beendet. Warte auf n√§chstes Signal.")

        -- Warten bis das Signal wieder aus ist (Flankenerkennung)
        while redstone.getInput(TRIGGER_SIDE) do
            sleep(0.1)
        end
    end

    sleep(0.1)
end

title: Notes
content:
-- Musikcomputer.lua
-- CC:Tweaked Musiksystem (mit BPM, Filterung & synchronisiertem Start)
-- Version 2.0

local CONFIG_FILE = "config.txt"
local CONTROL_FILE = "disk/control.txt"
local SONG_PATH_PREFIX = "disk/song_"
local instrumentConfig = {}

-- -----------------------------
-- Hilfsfunktionen
-- -----------------------------
local function fileExists(path)
    local f = fs.open(path, "r")
    if f then f.close() return true else return false end
end

local function saveConfig(config)
    local f = fs.open(CONFIG_FILE, "w")
    for k, v in pairs(config) do
        f.writeLine(k .. "=" .. v)
    end
    f.close()
end

local function loadConfig()
    local config = {}
    local f = fs.open(CONFIG_FILE, "r")
    if not f then return nil end
    for line in f.readLine do
        local key, value = line:match("^(.-)=(.*)$")
        if key and value then
            config[key] = value
        end
    end
    f.close()
    return config
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Initialisierung
-- -----------------------------
local function initialize()
    print("Keine Konfiguration gefunden. Initialisierung startet...")
    local config = {}

    write("Instrumentname: ")
    config.name = read()

    local sides = {"front", "right", "back", "left"}
    for _, side in ipairs(sides) do
        write("Ton an Seite '" .. side .. "' (z.B. C#2 oder none): ")
        config[side] = read()
    end

    saveConfig(config)
    print("Konfiguration gespeichert.")
    return config
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Lied laden (inkl. BPM)
-- -----------------------------
local function loadSong(instrumentName)
    local songPath = SONG_PATH_PREFIX .. instrumentName .. ".txt"
    if not fs.exists(songPath) then
        error("Songdatei nicht gefunden: " .. songPath)
    end

    local f = fs.open(songPath, "r")
    local bpm = 120
    local notes = {}

    while true do
        local line = f.readLine()
        if not line then break end

        if line:match("^BPM=") then
            bpm = tonumber(line:match("BPM=(%d+)"))
        elseif not (line:match("^#") or line == "") then
            local tonePart, length = line:match("^(.-)|(%d+)$")
            if tonePart and length then
                local tones = {}
                for tone in string.gmatch(tonePart, "([^,]+)") do
                    table.insert(tones, tone)
                end
                table.insert(notes, {tones = tones, length = tonumber(length)})
            end
        end
    end
    f.close()
    return bpm, notes
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Filter nach bespielbaren Noten
-- -----------------------------
local function filterSong(song, config, bpm)
    local playable = {}
    local sideNotes = {}
    for _, side in ipairs({"front", "right", "back", "left"}) do
        if config[side] and config[side] ~= "none" then
            sideNotes[config[side]] = side
        end
    end

    local function noteLengthToSeconds(noteValue, bpm)
        return (4 / noteValue) * (60 / bpm)
    end

    for _, entry in ipairs(song) do
        local validTones = {}
        for _, tone in ipairs(entry.tones) do
            if sideNotes[tone] then
                table.insert(validTones, tone)
            end
        end

        if #validTones > 0 then
            table.insert(playable, {
                tones = validTones,
                length = noteLengthToSeconds(entry.length, bpm)
            })
        else
            table.insert(playable, {
                tones = {"REST"},
                length = noteLengthToSeconds(entry.length, bpm)
            })
        end
    end

    return playable, sideNotes
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Steuerdatei lesen
-- -----------------------------
local function readControlFile()
    if not fileExists(CONTROL_FILE) then return false, 0 end

    local f = fs.open(CONTROL_FILE, "r")
    local play = false
    local startTime = 0

    while true do
        local line = f.readLine()
        if not line then break end
        local key, val = line:match("^(.-)=(.*)$")
        if key == "play" then
            play = (val == "true")
        elseif key == "startTime" then
            startTime = tonumber(val)
        end
    end
    f.close()
    return play, startTime
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Song abspielen
-- -----------------------------
local function playSong(filtered, sideNotes)
    for _, entry in ipairs(filtered) do
        if entry.tones[1] == "REST" then
            sleep(entry.length)
        else
            -- Redstone aktivieren
            for _, tone in ipairs(entry.tones) do
                local side = sideNotes[tone]
                if side then redstone.setOutput(side, true) end
            end

            sleep(0.001)

            -- Redstone deaktivieren
            for _, tone in ipairs(entry.tones) do
                local side = sideNotes[tone]
                if side then redstone.setOutput(side, false) end
            end

            -- Rest der Notenl√§nge warten
            local remaining = entry.length - 0.001
            if remaining > 0 then sleep(remaining) end
        end
    end
end

-- -----------------------------
-- Hauptprogramm
-- -----------------------------
if fileExists(CONFIG_FILE) then
    instrumentConfig = loadConfig()
    print("Konfiguration geladen f√ºr Instrument: " .. instrumentConfig.name)
else
    instrumentConfig = initialize()
end

print("Lade Song von Disk...")
local bpm, song = loadSong(instrumentConfig.name)
print("Song geladen (" .. #song .. " Schritte) mit BPM = " .. bpm)

print("Filtere Song f√ºr bespielbare Noten...")
local filtered, sideNotes = filterSong(song, instrumentConfig, bpm)
print("Gefilterter Song enth√§lt " .. #filtered .. " Eintr√§ge.")

print("Warte auf Startsignal...")

while true do
    local play, startTime = readControlFile()
    if play then
        local current = os.epoch("utc")
        local diff = startTime - current
        if diff > 0 then
            print("Starte Song in " .. string.format("%.2f", diff / 1000) .. " Sekunden...")
            sleep(diff / 1000)
        end

        print("Starte Abspielen!")
        playSong(filtered, sideNotes)
        print("Song beendet.")
        break
    end

    sleep(0.2) -- Systemschonende Abfrage
end

monitor = peripheral.wrap("monitor_1")
function pos(...) return term.setCursorPos(...) end
function cls(...) return term.clear() end
function tCol(...) return term.setTextColor(...) end
function bCol(...) return term.setBackgroundColor(...) end
function box(...) return paintutils.drawFilledBox(...) end
function line(...) return paintutils.drawLine(...) end
function write(...) return term.write(...) end
term.redirect(monitor)
w, h = monitor.getSize()

function getSize() w,h = monitor.getSize() end
tCol(colors.white)
local darkmode = true
local darkmodec

local boolArray = {false,false,false,false,false,false,false,false,false,false,false}

local function brf2()
    monitor.setTextScale(1.5)
    getSize()
    cls()
    if darkmode then darkmodec = colours.black else darkmodec = colours.blue end
    box(1,1,w,h,darkmodec)
    pos(w/2-#"BRF2"/2,1)
    write("BRF2")

    -- left column (6)
    local y=3
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Shimmer Dust") if boolArray[1]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Certus Quartz") if boolArray[2]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Certus Quartz Dust") if boolArray[3]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Shimmer") if boolArray[4]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Amethyst Dust") if boolArray[5]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Glow Ink Sac") if boolArray[6]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Ink Sac") if boolArray[7]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Paper") if boolArray[8]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    pos(5,y) bCol(darkmodec) write("Clay Dust") if boolArray[9]==false then box(23,y,26,y,colors.red) else box(23,y,26,y,colors.lime) end; y=y+2
    -- right column (5)
    local y2=3
    pos(28,y2) bCol(darkmodec) write("Lime Dust") if boolArray[10]==false then box(46,y2,49,y2,colors.red) else box(46,y2,49,y2,colors.lime) end; y2=y2+2
    pos(28,y2) bCol(darkmodec) write("Dried Kelp") if boolArray[11]==false then box(46,y2,49,y2,colors.red) else box(46,y2,49,y2,colors.lime) end

    pos(1,h) bCol(colors.black) write("EXIT")
    while true do
        local event, button, mx, my = os.pullEvent()
        if event == "monitor_touch" then
            if mx >= 1 and mx <= (1+#"EXIT") and my == h then return "menu" end
            local ly=3
            for i=1,9 do if mx>=23 and mx<=26 and my==ly then boolArray[i]=not boolArray[i]; brf2() end; ly=ly+2 end
            local ry=3
            for i=10,11 do if mx>=46 and mx<=49 and my==ry then boolArray[i]=not boolArray[i]; brf2() end; ry=ry+2 end
            if mx >= w/2-#"BRF2"/2 and mx <= w/2+#"BRF2"/2 and my == 1 then darkmode = not darkmode; brf2() end
        end
    end
end

return {brf2 = brf2}

    if boolArray[8]==false then box(23,17,26,17,colors.red) else box(23,17,26,17,colors.lime) end
    pos(5,19) bCol(darkmodec) write("Redstone Chip")
    if boolArray[9]==false then box(23,19,26,19,colors.red) else box(23,19,26,19,colors.lime) end

    -- right column   

    pos(1,h) bCol(colors.black) write("EXIT")
    while true do
        local event, button, mx, my = os.pullEvent()
        if event == "monitor_touch" then
            if mx >= 1 and mx <= (1+#"EXIT") and my == h then return "menu" end
            -- left toggles
            local ly = 3
            for i=1,9 do if mx >= 23 and mx <= 26 and my == ly then boolArray[i]=not boolArray[i]; electronics() end; ly=ly+2 end
            -- right toggles
            if mx >= w/2-#"ELECTRONICS"/2 and mx <= w/2+#"ELECTRONICS"/2 and my == 1 then darkmode = not darkmode; electronics() end
        end
    end
end

return {electronics = electronics}

term.redirect(monitor)
w, h = monitor.getSize()
local foundrya = require("foundry")
local dyea = require("dye")
local blocksa = require("blocks")
local loga = require("log")
local basicsa = require("basics")
--local brf1a = require("brf1")
local nethera = require("nether")
local electronicsa = require("electronics")
local brf2a = require("brf2")


function getSize() w,h = monitor.getSize() end
tCol(colors.white)
local andes = false
local darkmode = true
local darkmodec
------------------------------------------------------------

function drawMenu()
    monitor.setTextScale(2)
    getSize()
    bCol(colors.blue)
    if darkmode then
        box(1,1,w,h,colors.blue)
    else
        box(1,1,w,h,colors.blue)
    end
    
    pos(w/2-#"MENU"/2,1)
    write("MENU")

    monitor.setBackgroundColor(colors.lightGray)
    pos(5,3)
    write("FOUNDRY")
    pos(5,6)
    write("DYE")
    pos(5,9)
    write("BLOCKS")
    pos(5,12)
    write("LOG")
    pos(5,15)
    write("BASICS")
    pos(w/2,3)
    write("BRF1")
    pos(w/2,6)
    write("NETHER")
    pos(w/2,9)
    write("ELECTRONICS")
    pos(w/2,12)
    write("BRF2")
    pos(w/2,15)
    write("IRF")
    pos(1,17)
    bCol(colors.black)
    write("EXIT")
    bCol(colors.blue)

end

function main()
    drawMenu()
    
    while true do
    
        local event, button, mx, my = os.pullEvent()
        if event == "monitor_touch" then
        
            if mx >= 5 and mx <= (5+#"FOUNDRY") and my == 3 then
                foundrya.foundry()
                if foundrya.foundry() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            if mx >= 5 and mx <= (5+#"DYE") and my == 6 then
                dyea.dye()
                if dyea.dye() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            if mx >= 5 and mx <= (5+#"BLOCKS") and my == 9 then
                blocksa.blocks()
                if blocksa.blocks() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            if mx >= 5 and mx <= (5+#"LOG") and my == 12 then
                loga.log()
                if loga.log() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            if mx >= 5 and mx <= (5+#"BASICS") and my == 15 then
                basicsa.basics()
                if basicsa.basics() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
           --[[ if mx >= w/2 and mx <= (w/2+#"BRF1") and my == 3 then
                brf1a.brf1()
                if brf1a.brf1() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end--]]
            if mx >= w/2 and mx <= (w/2+#"NETHER") and my == 6 then
                nethera.nether()
                if nethera.nether() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            if mx >= w/2 and mx <= (w/2+#"ELECTRONICS") and my == 9 then
                electronicsa.electronics()
                if electronicsa.electronics() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            if mx >= w/2 and mx <= (w/2+#"BRF2") and my == 12 then
                brf2a.brf2()
                if brf2a.brf2() == "menu" then
                    drawMenu()
                end
            end
            
        end
    end 
end

--------------------------------------------------------------

local reactorName = "BiggerReactors_Reactor_1"
local maxTemp = 2200
local minTemp = 1800

local turbineName = "BiggerReactors_Turbine_0"
local targetRPM = 1800
local stepSize = 10

local checkInterval = 0.1
 
local mon = peripheral.wrap("monitor_2")
term.redirect(mon)
 
local reactor = peripheral.wrap(reactorName)
if not reactor then
  error("Reactor not found: " .. reactorName)
end
 
local turbine = peripheral.wrap(turbineName)
if not turbine then
  error("Turbine not found: " .. turbineName)
end
 
while true do
  local rodPercent = 100 * math.max(reactor.getCasingTemperature() - minTemp, 0) / (maxTemp - minTemp)
  reactor.setAllControlRodLevels(rodPercent)
  
  local rpm = turbine.rotor().RPM()
  
  if rpm > targetRPM then
	turbine.fluidTank().setNominalFlowRate(turbine.fluidTank().nominalFlowRate() - stepSize)
  else
	turbine.fluidTank().setNominalFlowRate(turbine.fluidTank().nominalFlowRate() + stepSize)
  end  
  
  if turbine.battery().stored() / turbine.battery().capacity() < 0.2 then
    if not reactor.active() then
      reactor.setActive(true)
      print("Reactor ON")
    end
  elseif turbine.battery().stored() / turbine.battery().capacity() > 0.8 then
    if reactor.active() then
      reactor.setActive(false)
      print("Reactor OFF")
    end
  end
  
  term.clear()
  term.setCursorPos(1,1)
  
  print("Temperature: " .. math.floor(reactor.fuelTemperature()))
  print("Rods: " .. math.floor(reactor.getControlRod(0).level()))
  sleep(checkInterval)
end

local RS = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")
local rebirth = RS:WaitForChild("RequestCompletionRebirth")

local maps = workspace.Maps
local mapId = 1
local found = maps and maps:FindFirstChild("Map"..mapId)
local burger = found and found.burger

local plr = game.Players.LocalPlayer

local stopped = false

local function re(h)
    if h then 
        h.Health = 0 
    end
end

plr.Chatted:Connect(function(msg)
    if msg == "StopInit" then 
        stopped = true 
    end
end)

while true do
    if stopped then 
        break 
    end
    local character = plr.Character or plr.CharacterAdded:Wait() 
    if character and burger then
        local humanoid = character:FindFirstChildOfClass("Humanoid") 
        character:PivotTo(burger:GetPivot())
        wait(0.5)
        local proximity = burger:FindFirstChild("ProximityPrompt")
        if proximity then
            proximity:InputHoldBegin()
            local triggered = false
            proximity.Triggered:Connect(function() 
                triggered = true 
            end)   
            local startTime = tick()
            while not triggered and (tick() - startTime) < 1 do
                wait(0.1)
            end
            if triggered then
                wait(1)
                rebirth:FireServer()
                wait(3)
            else
                re(humanoid)
                wait(5)
            end
        else
            re(humanoid)
            wait(5)
        end
    else
        re(humanoid)
        wait(5)
    end
end

title: Turbine control 2
content:
-- Peripheral setup
local modem = peripheral.find("modem") or error("No modem found", 0)
local monitor = peripheral.wrap("front") or error("No monitor on front", 0)

-- Monitor setup
monitor.setTextScale(0.5)
monitor.setBackgroundColor(colors.cyan)
monitor.clear()

local function drawLabel(y, text)
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, y)
    monitor.clearLine()
    monitor.write(text)
end

local function drawUI()
    drawLabel(4, "Fuel Feed")
    drawLabel(5, "-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-")
    drawLabel(8, "Clutch")
    drawLabel(9, "-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-")
    drawLabel(12, "Output")
    drawLabel(13, "-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-")
    monitor.setCursorPos(4, 1)
    monitor.write("Turbine #1")
end

drawUI()

term.clear()
term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
print("Running...")

-- Core Functions
local function transmitAndDisplay(channelOut, channelIn, mode, yPos, bgColor, side, pulse)
    if side then rs.setOutput(side, true) end
    modem.transmit(channelOut, channelIn, mode)
    monitor.setCursorPos(1, yPos)
    monitor.clearLine()
    monitor.blit(mode, ("0"):rep(#mode), bgColor)
    if pulse then sleep(1); if side then rs.setOutput(side, false) end end
end

local function fuelFeed(side, mode, bgColor)
    transmitAndDisplay(3, 4, mode, 6, bgColor, side, true)
end

local function shift(side, mode, bgColor)
    rs.setOutput("left", false)
    transmitAndDisplay(2, 3, mode, 10, bgColor, side, false)
end

local function modemCall(channel, callback)
    modem.open(channel)
    local _, _, _, _, message = os.pullEvent("modem_message")
    modem.close(channel)
    if callback then callback(message) end
    return message
end

local function battCall()
    return tonumber(modemCall(4, function(msg)
        term.setCursorPos(1, 2)
        term.clearLine()
        print(msg)
    end)) or 0
end

local function outputCall()
    modemCall(5, function(msg)
        monitor.setCursorPos(1, 14)
        monitor.clearLine()
        monitor.write(msg)
    end)
end

-- Main control loop
local inject, delay = 0, 0

while not rs.getInput("front") do
    local batt = battCall()
    local speed = rs.getAnalogInput("right")

    outputCall()

    if inject == 1 then delay = delay + 1 end
    if delay >= 280 then inject, delay = 0, 0 end

    if speed == 0 then
        shift("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        if batt <= 30 and inject == 0 then
            fuelFeed("bottom", "Engaged", "ddddddd")
            inject = 1
        elseif batt >= 35 then
            fuelFeed("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        end
    elseif speed <= 8 then
        shift("top", "Low RPM", "1111111")
        if batt >= 35 then
            fuelFeed("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        end
    else
        shift("left", "Engaged", "ddddddd")
        if batt >= 35 then
            fuelFeed("top", "Offline", "eeeeeee")
        end
    end
end
